### Remove an Element
```js  
//  Select Child and Store it into Variable
elementToRemove = document.getElementById("vespa");
//  Target Parent and Remove it from there
document.getElementById("italy-attractions").removeChild(elementToRemove)
```



### Hide an Element

```js 
//  Select Child and Store it into Variable
elementToRemove = document.getElementById("vespa");
// Hide it 
elementToRemove.hidden = true;
```


### Remove Child / Remove


> Difference between remove and removeChild

- `remove` only needs a reference to the child. 
- `removeChild` needs a reference both to the parent and the child. The result is identical.
